\section{Results}


Figure~\ref{fig:rates_modelled_2016_Baseline} shows modelled estimates of mortality rates in 2016.  The vertical bars are 95\% credible intervals: under the assumptions of the model, there is a 95\% probability that the true rate lie within the associated interval. The modelled estimates are substantially more regular and interpretable than the original direct estimates show in Figure~\ref{fig:rates_direct_2016}. Close inspection indicates that rates for are similar across states and territories, but not identical.

