Based on the modelled mortality rates, we generate life tables for each combination of sex, indigenous status, region, and time.  Life expectancies at birth from these life tables are shown in Figure~\ref{fig:life_expectancy_Baseline}, along with 95\% credible intervals. Although indigenous life expectancies are lower than non-indigenous ones in all states and territories, the difference is particularly pronounced in the Northern Territory.


